Reasoning: The paper describes experiments with a self-delimiting recurrent neural network that learns to solve self-invented problems and continually adds new problem-solving procedures to its skill repertoire. This falls under the domains of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and machine learning (cs.LG). The system also affects the environment through effectors, which relates to the field of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the system's ability to self-modularize and reuse code relates to the field of robotics (cs.RO).
